<refentry id="bif.Flatten" xreflabel="Flatten">

<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>Flatten</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>Flatten</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>Flatten</refname>
<refpurpose>
Removes nesting from a list
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
Flatten[x->NLIST(T*), {levels->0}] =: LIST(T) 
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>Flatten</function> returns a list with the same elements as
<parameter>x</parameter>, with the nesting
structure flattened.  By default, all levels are flattened, returning
a one-dimensional list; the optional parameter <parameter>levels</parameter> may be
used to limit the flattening to the topmost <parameter>levels</parameter>.
</para>
</refsect1>

</refentry>


